{"node_id": "0d6df740", "title": "Do not wrap `interrupt` calls in try/except", "path": "interrupts > Interrupts > Rules of interrupts > Do not wrap `interrupt` calls in try/except", "content": "The way that [`interrupt`](https://reference.langchain.com/python/langgraph/types/#langgraph.types.interrupt) pauses execution at the point of the call is by throwing a special exception. If you wrap the [`interrupt`](https://reference.langchain.com/python/langgraph/types/#langgraph.types.interrupt) call in a try/except block, you will catch this exception and the interrupt will not be passed back to the graph.\n\n* ‚úÖ Separate [`interrupt`](https://reference.langchain.com/python/langgraph/types/#langgraph.types.interrupt) calls from error-prone code\n* ‚úÖ Use specific exception types in try/except blocks\n\n<CodeGroup>\n  ```python Separating logic theme={null}\n  def node_a(state: State):\n      # ‚úÖ Good: interrupting first, then handling\n      # error conditions separately\n      interrupt(\"What's your name?\")\n      try:\n          fetch_data()  # This can fail\n      except Exception as e:\n          print(e)\n      return state\n  ```\n\n  ```python Explicit exception handling theme={null}\n  def node_a(state: State):\n      # ‚úÖ Good: catching specific exception types\n      # will not catch the interrupt exception\n      try:\n          name = interrupt(\"What's your name?\")\n          fetch_data()  # This can fail\n      except NetworkException as e:\n          print(e)\n      return state\n  ```\n</CodeGroup>\n\n* üî¥ Do not wrap [`interrupt`](https://reference.langchain.com/python/langgraph/types/#langgraph.types.interrupt) calls in bare try/except blocks\n\n```python  theme={null}\ndef node_a(state: State):\n    # ‚ùå Bad: wrapping interrupt in bare try/except\n    # will catch the interrupt exception\n    try:\n        interrupt(\"What's your name?\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(e)\n    return state\n```", "summary": "Explains that wrapping `interrupt` calls in bare try/except blocks prevents proper graph execution, as `interrupt` uses a special exception to pause. Recommends separating `interrupt` from error handling or using specific exception types.", "keywords": ["interrupt", "try/except", "exception", "graph execution", "pause", "error handling", "NetworkException", "State", "langgraph", "interrupt exception"]}